latestPosts.caption:
This was a trip highlight for me at @emboocamp 

We were on a sunrise safari when we spotted this Cheetah perched on top of a termite mound - she was scouting the landscape for prey and I couldn’t believe I was seeing this in real life 

Cheetahs were the animal I was most excited to see so on our trip so I was absolutely frothing to get this shot 

@sonyalpha A7IV 200-600G + 2x Teleconverter for the portrait

latestPosts.caption:
Owls are my favourite bird and I have been on the lookout for one in the wild for so long.

We were almost back to the trailhead at Skookumchuck Narrows when we spotted this stunning Barred Owl on a tree right above us.

I was frothing to finally see an Owl and to watch it hunting in the forest completely unfazed by us was such a rad experience.

@sonyalpha A7IV & 200-600G

latestPosts.caption:
We were having a couple of lunch tuskers by the pool at @serenahotels in Amboseli when we found this sick Kenyan Rock Agama. The colours on this lizard are hectic.

Another guest came over and got just as excited as we were to see the rainbow dinosaur and asked if I’d like to get a photo with it - who could resist

latestPosts.caption:
We even got to see it hunting!! 

Coastal BC always delivers such incredible wildlife encounters but given my love and appreciation for owls, this was extra special. This is a barred owl! As you can hear, the others birds around us were going off and it was amazing to just sit back and watch nature do its thing. 

The photos in this video were taken by the very talented @jaybaumann.photos 🌿
